About Me

I'm a Master's student in Business Analytics (aka Data Science for Businesses) at Rady School of Management at UC San Diego. Prior to my master's, I did my undergraduate at UC San Diego in International Studies - Economics, where I first encountered simple regression models in Econometrics class. I soon became fascinated by what we can with Data, and since then, I have been working my way out to become an effective Data Scientist. In my master's, I am learning Business-focused analytics (e.g., Customer analytics, Fraud analytics, Pricing Analytics), Data Science methodologies (e.g., Baysian learning, Working with unstructured data), and Big Data tools (e.g., SQL, Hadoop, Cloud computing)

I currently work as a Data Analyst for The Neurosciences Department at UC San Diego. Speficically, I work for The Study of Latinos - Investigation of Neurocognitive Aging (SOL-INCA), where I implement survey generalized models to investigate hypothesized associations between Neurocognitive aging and other health conditions. Software Engineer

Besides my computer science knowledge, three things that make me an effective software engineer are that I am an excellent communicator, always eager to learn more, and very pragmatic. Since I will graduate in May 2022, I am actively seeking an internship role as a Software Engineer. If my background aligns with the type of engineer you are searching for, then please contact me. If you're not convinced yet, then please check out my LinkedIn or resume.

) }; export default About;
